A schedule credit up to this % may be applied based on the underwriter's judgment. The
purpose of this credit is to recognize risk characteristics that are not reflected in the otherwise
applicable premium. The underwriter should consider the following in determining whether
to apply a schedule credit:
a. The historical loss experience of the applicant;
b. Claim anomalies in the historical loss experience;
c. The cumulative number of years of patient experience;
d. Management control procedures.
